 equipment acquired but not yet paid | ~$10.2B |\n\n## Forward-Looking 2026 Capex Guidance\n\nThe filing provides **qualitative but not quantitative** guidance for 2026:\n\n1. **From the Investing Activities discussion**: Amazon explicitly states that cash capital expenditures for both technology infrastructure (AWS) and fulfillment network capacity are **"expected to increase in 2026"** — implying capex above the $128.3B/$131.8B level reported for 2025.\n\n2. **From the Q1 2026 guidance section**: Operating income guidance of $16.5B–$21.5B includes "approximately $1 billion of higher year-over-year Amazon Leo costs as we scale in 2026, as well as investment in quick commerce and even sharper prices in our international stores business" — but no specific dollar figure for capex is provided.\n\n3. **No specific dollar guidance** for 2026 total capital expenditures (including or excluding finance leases) is disclosed in the chunks provided.',
